    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I can't remember presently, but is `TermResponse` able to handle kitty query codes? I know that I had to suppress the responses when sending terminal escape codes because neovim could not handle the responses, which would break the TUI.\n\nWhen I was working on #31399, I remember that I couldn't capture responses to terminal size queries, and I seem to remember also not being able to handle any kitty responses. If we can unlock that, it means we'll also be able to properly check that an image with a specific id is still in the terminal's cache (separate feature for optimization).\n\nCalling out here because the reason I didn't introduce this support in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30889 was because I thought neovim's `TermResponse` didn't work with it (yet).",
            "created_at": "2026-04-27T04:01:34Z",
